thread.title: Southwest Completes Engine Inspections

author: Doug Cameron
title: Southwest Completes Engine Inspections
text:
ANNAPOLIS, Md.â€”Southwest Airlines Co. said it has completed engine inspections across its fleet of more than 700 jets after a fatal accident on one of its flights last month.
Chief Executive Gary Kelly on Wednesday said Southwest has sent a small number of engine fan blades back to their maker for further tests and is working with manufacturers and regulators on the potential redesign of parts and inspection protocols.
